text: The 2020 United States presidential election in Florida was held on Tuesday, November 3, 2020, as part of the 2020 United States presidential election. Incumbent President Donald Trump and his running mate, Vice President Mike Pencehad won 29 electoral votes in the Electoral College. == References == Category:2020 United States presidential election Category:2020s in Florida
title: 2020 United States presidential election in Florida
